Create a function called printGreeting that takes one string typed argument (firstName) and it prints out a Hello greeting. Override the printGreeting function that it can also take two arguments firstName and lastName. Call the both functions using firstName = John and lastName = Johnson values.


Example output:
Hello John
Hello John Johnson
The verification of program output does not account for whitespace characters like "\n", "\t" and " "

//solution

fun main(args: Array<String>) {
	printGreeting("John")
	printGreeting("John", "Johnson")
}
fun printGreeting(firstName: String){
	println("Hello $firstName")
}
fun printGreeting(firstName: String, lastName: String){
	println("Hello $firstName $lastName")
}
